trans-unit.source: Defines identifiers for the standard set of commands that are available to most applications.
This class defines <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> identifiers for standard commands that are available to designers.

To add a command from the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.StandardCommands> class to a designer menu, you must call the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IMenuCommandService.AddCommand%2A> method of an <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IMenuCommandService> and add a <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.MenuCommand> that contains a <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> from <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.StandardCommands>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.Design.StandardCommands"></xref> class.

Gets the first of a set of verbs.
This field is read-only.
This is a special <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> that identifies the first of a set of designer verbs.

The Visual Studio Windows Forms Designer automatically maps designer verbs to the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IDesigner.Verbs%2A> property on <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IDesigner>, so generally you do not need to access this command.

All designer verbs for an object become commands with a <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> within a sequential range of IDs that begins with <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.StandardCommands.VerbFirst> and ends with <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.StandardCommands.VerbLast>.
Gets the last of a set of verbs.
This field is read-only.
This is a special <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> that identifies the last of a set of designer verbs.

The Visual Studio Windows Forms Designer automatically maps designer verbs to the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IDesigner.Verbs%2A> property on <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IDesigner>, so generally you do not need to access this command.
